Title: Crossref title-only search returns wrong candidates for short titles
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-28
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-28T14:32Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

Direct probe of `https://api.crossref.org/works?query.title=Incentivising+CCS+in+the+EU&rows=5` returned:

```
cand0: 'EU executive launches CCS support network'
cand1: 'Kontextualisierende Verortung: CCS in der EU-Klimapolitik'
cand2: 'Incentivising Angels'
cand3: ...
cand4: ...
```

None of these is the actual paper. The right candidate is either
buried beyond rank 5 or absent from the top-N. The MAIBA Crossref
resolver currently passes only `query.title` with `rows=5` — too
narrow for short, generic titles.

This is not a threshold-tuning issue. The scorer is correctly
rejecting the noise (returns `None` for each candidate). The fix is
in query construction, not scoring.

Verified bug, not hypothetical. Affects 6 of 7 JOUR misses on
`tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris`: they all have short titles and
their right candidates do not appear in Crossref's top-5 by
relevance score alone.

## Actions

1. **Year filter when `item.PY` is present** — Crossref accepts
   `filter=from-pub-date:YYYY-01-01,until-pub-date:YYYY-12-31`.
   Use `PY ± 1` as the window to absorb minor cataloging drift
   (DOI registered 1 year off the publication year, cross-volume
   articles, etc.):
   ```python
   if item.PY:
       params["filter"] = (
           f"from-pub-date:{item.PY-1}-01-01,"
           f"until-pub-date:{item.PY+1}-12-31"
       )
   ```
   This narrows the pool dramatically for short-titled papers.

2. **Increase `rows` to 20** (configurable):
   ```yaml
   crossref:
     search_rows: 20            # was hard-coded 5
   ```
   Crossref is free; doubling the candidate window costs nothing.
   The shared scorer still rejects the bottom of the list.

3. **Add `query.author` when partial AU is present** — even for the
   AU-missing cases, sometimes a single author lastname is in the
   record. If `item.AU` has any non-forbidden entry, pass the
   first author's lastname as `query.author`:
   ```python
   first = next((a for a in (item.AU or []) if "et al" not in a.lower()), None)
   if first:
       params["query.author"] = _extract_lastname(first)
   ```

4. **`config/maiba.yaml`** additions:
   ```yaml
   crossref:
     search_rows: 20
     year_window: 1   # PY ± window for filter
   ```

5. **Same expansion for OpenAlex** — symmetric problem, symmetric
   fix. OpenAlex already has `filter=publication_year:YYYY` on exact
   year; widen to `publication_year:YYYY-1|YYYY|YYYY+1` (OpenAlex
   accepts pipe-separated). And `per_page` from 5 to 20.

## Test (TDD red step)

```python
# tests/test_resolve_crossref.py — additions
import respx
from httpx import Response
from maiba.config import load_config
from maiba.model import Item
from maiba.resolvers.crossref import CrossrefResolver

CFG = load_config(Path("config/maiba.yaml"))


@respx.mock
def test_crossref_passes_year_filter_when_PY_present():
    captured = {}
    def callback(request):
        captured["params"] = dict(request.url.params)
        return Response(200, json={"message": {"items": []}})
    respx.get(url__startswith="https://api.crossref.org/works").mock(side_effect=callback)

    resolver = CrossrefResolver(CFG)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="Incentivising CCS in the EU", AU=[], PY=2010)
    resolver.resolve(item)

    f = captured["params"].get("filter", "")
    assert "from-pub-date:2009-01-01" in f
    assert "until-pub-date:2011-12-31" in f


@respx.mock
def test_crossref_uses_configured_rows():
    captured = {}
    def callback(request):
        captured["params"] = dict(request.url.params)
        return Response(200, json={"message": {"items": []}})
    respx.get(url__startswith="https://api.crossref.org/works").mock(side_effect=callback)

    resolver = CrossrefResolver(CFG)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="x", AU=[], PY=2020)
    resolver.resolve(item)
    assert int(captured["params"].get("rows", "0")) == CFG.crossref.search_rows


@respx.mock
def test_no_PY_means_no_year_filter():
    captured = {}
    def callback(request):
        captured["params"] = dict(request.url.params)
        return Response(200, json={"message": {"items": []}})
    respx.get(url__startswith="https://api.crossref.org/works").mock(side_effect=callback)

    resolver = CrossrefResolver(CFG)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="x", AU=["a"], PY=None)
    resolver.resolve(item)
    assert "filter" not in captured["params"]
```

## Exit criteria

- `make test` green.
- `make lint` green.
- Smoke run on the 7 JOUR misses (after ticket 0023 lands and OpenAlex
  is authed): at least 5 of 7 resolve, vs. 1 today (only the
  DOI-bearing one). Manual eyeball, not asserted.
- No hardcoded numbers in the resolver — `rows`, year window from
  config.

## Out of scope

- LLM-generated query rewriting. The current fix is mechanical
  (year filter + larger window + author hint when present); no LLM
  involved. If after this ticket recall is still <5/7 on the JOUR
  set, surface in the next iteration.
- Different relevance weighting on Crossref's side. Crossref's
  ranking is opaque to us; we have to live with what they return
  in the top-20. Any further tuning happens client-side via the
  scorer.
